<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4650657>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 3. — Restoration of the right suborbital (SO) plate of Atlantidosteus pacifica n. sp.; A, external surface; B, internal surface; C, section through the suborbital lamina at the level indicated (arrow in B). Abbreviations: att.aup, attachment surface for the autopalatine;?att.pq, possible attachment surface for the metapterygoid part of the palatoquadrate; cr1, 2, outer and inner crests on dorsal surface of suborbital process; cuso, cutaneous sensory organ; gr, groove; gr.mx, groove for the maxillary branch of the trigeminal nerve; gr.md, groove for the mandibular branch of the trigeminal nerve; gr.PtO/M, area abutting postorbital plate and/or marginal plate; hc, horizontal sensory groove; ioc.sb, suborbital section of infraorbital sensory groove; le, lesions or healed wounds on external surface; oaPtO, area overlapped by postorbital plate; pvpr, posteroventral process of SO plate; sbsp, suborbital sensory pits; so.la, suborbital lamina of SO plate; sorc, supraoral sensory groove. Scale bar: 10 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4650657/files/figure.png" .

