<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4650661>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 5. — Comparison of suborbital plates of Atlantidosteus Lelièvre, 1984 and Homostius Asmuss, 1856 (not to scale; reduced to same length), showing the extent of unornamented parts of external surface (shaded); A, Atlantidosteus hollardi Lelièvre, 1984; B, A. pacifica n. sp.; C, Homostius sp. Shaded areas in Homostius include those overlapped by the postorbital and marginal plates of the skull (dorsal margin), and those assumed to be embedded in soft tissue (ventral margin and suborbital lamina). A, based on Lelièvre (1984a: fig. 2A); C, based on Heintz (1934: fig. 22)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4650661/files/figure.png" .

